1
00:00:04,742 --> 00:00:08,229
Guru Mahārāj
in Gadādhar pranam

2
00:00:08,229 --> 00:00:13,662
says, “On the shore 
of that broad blue ocean,

3
00:00:13,918 --> 00:00:19,709
nīlāmbhodhi-taṭe sadā sva-virahā.”

4
00:00:19,709 --> 00:00:25,199
Sva-virahā— 
‘feeling separation from Himself’.

5
00:00:25,269 --> 00:00:28,068
[“You Will Faint!”]

6
00:00:28,639 --> 00:00:30,987
That’s how it’s expressed.

7
00:00:30,987 --> 00:00:34,190
Kṛṣṇa as Mahāprabhu 
feeling separation from Kṛṣṇa.

8
00:00:34,190 --> 00:00:39,054
The Supreme Positive 
in the mood of the Supreme Negative,

9
00:00:39,054 --> 00:00:42,122
plunging the depths 
of separation.

10
00:00:42,122 --> 00:00:45,647
Sva-virahā-kṣepanvitaṁ bāndhavaṁ,

11
00:00:45,647 --> 00:00:47,758
‘in the company 
of His dearmost friend’.

12
00:00:47,758 --> 00:00:50,619
Who’s His dearmost friend? 
Gadādhar Paṇḍit.

13
00:00:50,619 --> 00:00:55,948
Śrīmad-Bhāgavatī kathā 
madirayā sañjīvayan bhāti yaḥ.

14
00:00:55,948 --> 00:01:01,641
And what is Gadādhar Paṇḍit doing 
to relieve the anguish of separation

15
00:01:01,641 --> 00:01:03,303
in the heart of Mahāprabhu?

16
00:01:03,303 --> 00:01:06,155
We’re told, the tenth stage of separation 
is death.

17
00:01:06,155 --> 00:01:09,916
So Mahāprabhu is on the verge 
of death.

18
00:01:09,916 --> 00:01:12,569
Sañjīvayan.

19
00:01:12,569 --> 00:01:19,069
I told before, 
this one ayurvedic medicine

20
00:01:19,069 --> 00:01:22,125
Prabhupad’s kavirāj 
told me about—

21
00:01:22,125 --> 00:01:26,452
Kṛṣṇananda Tarkatīrtha Kavirāj.

22
00:01:26,452 --> 00:01:34,194
So this sañjīvayan, it will bring 
a dead person back to life.

23
00:01:34,194 --> 00:01:39,668
And we mean by that 
the recently dead.

24
00:01:39,668 --> 00:01:43,092
Sañjīva, this rasāyan,
this medicine,

25
00:01:43,092 --> 00:01:46,363
can bring someone 
on the verge of death back to life.

26
00:01:46,363 --> 00:01:50,066
Gadādhar Paṇḍit, 
Śrīmad-Bhāgavatī kathā madirayā,

27
00:01:50,066 --> 00:01:54,040
is taking Bhāgavat ślokas 
and supplying them

28
00:01:54,040 --> 00:01:57,673
—like certain medicines 
are intoxicants—

29
00:01:57,673 --> 00:01:59,986
like an intoxicating 
substance

30
00:01:59,986 --> 00:02:05,137
to bring relief 
to the heart of Mahāprabhu.

31
00:02:05,137 --> 00:02:09,811
That’s the Bhāgavatī kathā madirayā. 
Madirayā means ‘wine’.

32
00:02:09,811 --> 00:02:12,125
So, it means like that,

33
00:02:12,125 --> 00:02:15,455
when someone’s feelings 
are so distraught,

34
00:02:15,455 --> 00:02:19,691
devastated, heart-broken 
in the absence of their beloved,

35
00:02:19,722 --> 00:02:23,639
another friend comes supplying
an intoxicating beverage

36
00:02:23,639 --> 00:02:27,402
they can drink 
and get some relief.

37
00:02:27,402 --> 00:02:30,295
In this case, 
what is the intoxicating beverage?

38
00:02:30,295 --> 00:02:33,984
Bhāgavat ślokas, 
selecting Bhāgavat ślokas.

39
00:02:33,984 --> 00:02:36,643
This is how perfect 
Śrīla Guru Mahārāj is.

40
00:02:36,643 --> 00:02:42,359
This is his introduction 
to his Bhāgavat śloka selections

41
00:02:42,359 --> 00:02:45,768
under the inspiration 
of the Bhāgavatārka-marīchī mālā

42
00:02:45,768 --> 00:02:47,946
of Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur

43
00:02:47,946 --> 00:02:52,985
that came due to the inspiration
of Svarūp Dāmodar.

44
00:02:52,985 --> 00:02:54,920
Back to Svarūp Dāmodar,

45
00:02:54,920 --> 00:02:57,113
“Mahāprabhura dvitīya kalevara;

46
00:02:57,113 --> 00:03:00,185
Mahāprabhu the 2nd.” 
[Cc: 2.11.76]

47
00:03:01,155 --> 00:03:04,202
That Svarūp Dāmodar 
told Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur

48
00:03:04,202 --> 00:03:07,941
to collect these thousand 
Bhāgavat sun-rays.

49
00:03:07,941 --> 00:03:12,616
Bhāgavatārka-marīchī arka
purāṇārko 'dhunoditaḥ

50
00:03:12,616 --> 00:03:14,459
kalau naṣṭa-dṛśām eṣa
[SB: 1.3.43]

51
00:03:14,459 --> 00:03:16,535
Like an eighteen-thousand 
rayed sun,

52
00:03:16,535 --> 00:03:19,355
collect a thousand 
of those rays.

53
00:03:19,355 --> 00:03:24,233
Guru Mahārāj was going 
to further distil three or four-hundred.

54
00:03:24,233 --> 00:03:28,130
But what would be the criterion 
for selection?

55
00:03:28,130 --> 00:03:29,915
That’s all important.

56
00:03:29,915 --> 00:03:34,124
He’s giving a hint 
in this śloka.

57
00:03:34,630 --> 00:03:37,885
As Gadādhar Paṇḍit selects 
these ślokas

58
00:03:37,885 --> 00:03:42,534
to relieve the anguish of separation 
from Mahāprabhu,

59
00:03:42,534 --> 00:03:47,542
or in some instances, 
to augment certain sentiments.

60
00:03:47,542 --> 00:03:51,634
He’s giving a hint 
at the selection criteria.

61
00:03:51,634 --> 00:03:56,152
Śrīmad-bhāgavatī kathā 
madirayā sañjīvayan bhāti yaḥ

62
00:03:56,152 --> 00:04:02,455
Śrīmad-bhāgavataṁ sadā 
sva-nayanāśru-pāyanaiḥ pūjayan

63
00:04:03,814 --> 00:04:09,109
And saying, 
those Bhāgavat ślokas

64
00:04:09,602 --> 00:04:12,260
are like, are doing this,

65
00:04:16,251 --> 00:04:21,263
that tears are pouring 
from the eyes of Gadādhar Paṇḍit

66
00:04:21,263 --> 00:04:27,184
like lotus flower offerings 
onto the pages of the Bhāgavatam,

67
00:04:27,184 --> 00:04:30,090
where those ślokas are written.

68
00:04:30,090 --> 00:04:35,426
And once they’re spoken, 
and spoken in this particular way

69
00:04:35,426 --> 00:04:38,204
with this particular 
depth of meaning,

70
00:04:38,204 --> 00:04:40,190
the tears are falling 
onto the pages

71
00:04:40,190 --> 00:04:41,905
as if they’re flower offerings,

72
00:04:41,905 --> 00:04:44,747
and washing away the letters.

73
00:04:45,443 --> 00:04:51,044
The letters are washing off 
the pages

74
00:04:51,105 --> 00:04:58,582
as if they were never to be spoken again, 
or known in that way.

75
00:04:58,582 --> 00:05:01,089
Too sacred.

76
00:05:02,346 --> 00:05:07,515
So that when Śrīnivas Āchārya 
approached Gadādhar Paṇḍit

77
00:05:08,003 --> 00:05:12,140
for divine direction

78
00:05:12,248 --> 00:05:15,161
for Bhāgavat, to hear Bhāgavat,

79
00:05:15,161 --> 00:05:18,244
Gadādhar Paṇḍit said,
“What I want to teach you,

80
00:05:18,244 --> 00:05:22,777
my tears have washed away 
those ślokas.

81
00:05:22,777 --> 00:05:27,773
So, you need to go to Nabadwīp
and get a fresh copy.”

82
00:05:27,773 --> 00:05:29,704
Of course, Śrīnivas Āchārya 
goes to Nabadwīp,

83
00:05:29,704 --> 00:05:30,819
by the time he returns,

84
00:05:30,819 --> 00:05:34,024
Gadādhar Paṇḍit has left 
the world.

85
00:05:34,387 --> 00:05:36,502
Why does Kṛṣṇa do that?

86
00:05:36,502 --> 00:05:40,862
Why does Kṛṣṇa do things 
like that?

87
00:05:41,644 --> 00:05:46,041
If not to take the heart 
to greater depth,

88
00:05:46,041 --> 00:05:53,943
to have us achieve a greater depth 
of heart, feeling, devotion.

89
00:05:55,515 --> 00:06:00,127
The deep heart’s core.

90
00:06:03,834 --> 00:06:08,950
Gosvāmi-prabaro Gadādhara-vibhūr-bhūyāt 
mad-ekā-gatiḥ;

91
00:06:08,950 --> 00:06:10,250
So Guru Mahārāj says,

92
00:06:10,250 --> 00:06:14,472
“So let this book to be an offering 
to that best of Goswāmīs,

93
00:06:14,472 --> 00:06:16,693
Gadādhar Paṇḍit Goswāmī.”

94
00:06:16,693 --> 00:06:21,720
Gosvāmi-prabaro Gadādhara-vibhūr-bhūyāt 
mad-ekā-gatiḥ—

95
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:28,454
that’s the target of the offering 
of these prayers.

96
00:06:28,454 --> 00:06:32,236
So what is the position 
of Śrīla Guru Mahārāj

97
00:06:32,442 --> 00:06:37,356
that he can express such things?

98
00:06:38,695 --> 00:06:41,755
One day in the afternoon,

99
00:06:41,755 --> 00:06:43,862
there was Guru Mahārāj 
in his chair

100
00:06:43,862 --> 00:06:47,058
and Gurudev next to him,
and I came.

101
00:06:47,473 --> 00:06:50,462
Those were happy times.

102
00:06:51,937 --> 00:06:56,173
And I said to Gurudev,

103
00:07:00,028 --> 00:07:04,608
“Guru Mahārāj said that when 
Achyutānanda asked Swāmī Mahārāj,

104
00:07:04,608 --> 00:07:06,000
‘What did Śrīdhar Mahārāj 
say to you?’

105
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:08,550
He said, ‘If I told you, 
you would faint.’”

106
00:07:08,550 --> 00:07:13,123
I said, “I want to know, 
what are those things?”

107
00:07:14,489 --> 00:07:16,035
And Guru Mahārāj said, 
“What?”

108
00:07:16,035 --> 00:07:18,883
And then Gurudev 
started laughing,

109
00:07:18,883 --> 00:07:20,980
And Guru Mahārāj said, 
“What, what?”

110
00:07:20,980 --> 00:07:23,875
and Gurudev told him 
in Bengali,

111
00:07:23,875 --> 00:07:28,974
“Goswāmī Mahārāj wants
you to make him faint."

112
00:07:28,974 --> 00:07:31,314
[Laughs]

113
00:07:32,735 --> 00:07:37,272
And Guru Mahārāj [said], 
“Ācha.”

114
00:07:37,272 --> 00:07:39,507
And they start talking,

115
00:07:39,507 --> 00:07:44,760
like, what should they say, 
fainting śloka.

116
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:49,314
Then Guru Mahārāj explained 
this Gadādhar-praṇām,

117
00:07:49,314 --> 00:07:54,799
and what I’ve said here
is bākya-aparādh, an offence;

118
00:07:54,799 --> 00:07:57,840
can’t possibly represent how

119
00:07:57,840 --> 00:08:02,885
His Divine Grace expressed that 
at that time,

120
00:08:02,885 --> 00:08:06,668
but as he did that to me,

121
00:08:06,668 --> 00:08:11,320
I staggered away
from where the two of them were,

122
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:14,474
against the wall,
with my head against the wall,

123
00:08:14,474 --> 00:08:17,987
like, dragging my head 
against the wall,

124
00:08:17,987 --> 00:08:21,815
losing consciousness 
of the world.

125
00:08:21,923 --> 00:08:26,012
And Guru Mahārāj and Gurudev, 
they’re talking.

126
00:08:26,012 --> 00:08:28,971
I came back 
around 15 minutes later.

127
00:08:28,971 --> 00:08:30,731
[Laughs]

128
00:08:31,551 --> 00:08:34,416
To make me faint, was like,

129
00:08:35,049 --> 00:08:39,477
“This little boy, 
send the boy away.

130
00:08:40,570 --> 00:08:42,123
Come back.

131
00:08:43,336 --> 00:08:44,582
Later.”

